Optimization of striatal NGF cell models using cortical NGC
reconstructions from NMC portal (Blue Brain Project/EPFL)
and electrophysiology of Ibanez-Sandoval et al., 2011 (DOI:
10.1523/JNEUROSCI.2628-11.2011).

release/  validated models of the striatal NGF cells. See files
          `hall_of_fame.json` for the best electrical parameters,
          `morphology/*.swc` for morphological reconstructions and
          `validation/val_models.json` for validated morpho-electric
          combinations.

-------------------------------------------------------
The optimization was done using A. Kozlov's optim setup in repo:

	https://gitr.sys.kth.se/akozlov/bgmod.git

under branch:
	
	ngf_updated_fig4_optim

using folder:

	models/optim/ngf/optim/Roberts_optim
	
	
Otimization protocols can be found in the config folder

After optimization:
1. Use the notebooks to select models and update hall_of_fame.json
2. run variate.sh     (simulates p-m combinations, extracts features and writes to file)
3. run validate.sh	  (plot features and compare to exp data)

:::::::::::
After this the models were transferred from bpo to snudda using 

	simple_transfer.py

in bgdata/examples 
	
	https://github.com/Hjorthmedh/BasalGangliaData
	
like:

	BasalGangliaData/examples$ python simple_transfer.py -s <akozlov>/models/optim/ngf/optim/Roberts_optim/ -d <szmod>/snudda/snudda_data/wt/neurons/striatum/ngf/


-------------------------------
Apr -26: model selection pipeline updated

  Model selection history (NGF IS2011FIG4A):

  Starting point: 10 models from BluePyOpt optimization (hall_of_fame_orig.json, 2026-04-07)

  Step 1 — Visual inspection (select_v3_bmid9.ipynb, 2026-04-07)
    Original index 5 rejected: model went into depolarization block for the largest
    long current step, which is not physiologically plausible for this cell type.
    9 models saved to hall_of_fame.json; original 10 backed up as hall_of_fame_orig.json.

  Step 2 — Automated z-score validation (validate.py, 2026-04-09)
    Models run across stimulus range (variate.py), features scored against population
    statistics (IS2011 Table 1, mean ± std). Threshold: 3 standard deviations.
    Rejected models printed to stdout with offending features and z-scores.
    Backups written automatically as hall_of_fame_{YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS}_from_val.json.
    Current state of hall_of_fame.json: 5 models (as of 2026-04-09).

  Features scored:
    vm_rest, ir_fitrest (R_in at 0 pA), ap_avg_thresh, ap_half_width,
    ap_amplitude, ap_peak, ahp_depth_abs

  Feature derivation:
    vm_rest      -- eFEL voltage_base averaged across subthreshold steps
    ir_fitrest   -- slope of IV curve fit evaluated at 0 pA
    ap_avg_thresh, ap_half_width, ap_amplitude, ap_peak -- eFEL features
    ahp_depth_abs -- eFEL AHP_depth_abs (absolute AHP trough voltage)
                     For experimental data (IS2011 Table 1), derived as
                     AP threshold minus AHP amplitude (ap_avg_thresh - ahp_depth),
                     where ahp_depth is the paper definition (threshold - AHP min).

  Previously tracked AHP metrics (removed from scoring 2026-04-09):
    ahp_depth      -- paper definition: AP threshold - AHP minimum (26 ± 4.47 mV)
    ahp_depth_efel -- eFEL definition:  AHP minimum - voltage_base  (18 ± 7.61 mV)
    ahp_depth_abs  -- absolute AHP minimum voltage (-70 ± 6.24 mV;
                      std from error propagation of threshold and ahp_depth stds)

